Why to use bootstrap?
// The main purpose of using bootstrap instead of CSS is to minimize the code lengths and the file size;
=> Faster and more responsive website without having lengthy code;

How bootstrap works?
Bootstrap:- is a collection of different classes of CSS that are coded in a way that does
not add to the size of the file;
Limitation:--It offers limited options when it comes to colors;

Latest version:- 5.1x

How to use bootstrap in our project?
1. use CDN(content delivery network) link: Copy the given link in bootstrap website;
add this link in the head section:
<link
    href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
    rel="stylesheet"
    integrity="sha384-4bw+/aepP/YC94hEpVNVgiZdgIC5+VKNBQNGCHeKRQN+PtmoHDEXuppvnDJzQIu9"
    crossorigin="anonymous">

2. Download:
**Download the extension file from the website, and mention the path in the link tag under the head tag;
<link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="bootstrap-5.3.1-dist/css/bootstrap.css"
    />

BOOTSTRAP BREAKPOINTS:
https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/layout/breakpoints/;

How to customize properties in bootstrap:
Use important mark after the properties;

COL PROPERTIES IN BOOTSTRAP:
Bootstrap's Grid system;

*me- margin-right
*ms- margin start

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BUILDING RELTIO WEB MOCK UP:-

1. Add css cdn link in the head tag
2. Add js link at the last in the body tag;

3. Add navbar component from bootstrap; customize accordingly
